open-bastion (0.1.3) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Mode E hardening: tested end-to-end deployment
  * Fix PAM module name: pam_llng.so -> pam_openbastion.so
  * Fix NSS module symbols: _nss_llng_* -> _nss_openbastion_*
  * Fix NSS config: nsswitch.conf uses 'openbastion', server_token_file key
  * Fix ob-enroll: send client_secret to device endpoint (optional)
  * Fix ob-bastion-setup: add Include directive, AuthorizedPrincipalsCommand,
    PermitRootLogin no, NSS configuration, pam_mkhomedir.so
  * Fix session recorder paths: ob-session-recorder, /etc/open-bastion/
  * Fix sudo Mode E: remove pam_unix.so from account (NSS-only users),
    create /etc/sudoers.d/open-bastion
  * Session recording privilege separation via setgid wrapper
    (ob-session-recorder-wrapper, group ob-sessions, mode 1770)
  * New risk R-S18: session recording tampering (mitigated P=1/I=1)
  * Pre-hardening bootstrap: securetty ttyS0, PermitRootLogin no,
    service account for emergency access

 -- Xavier Guimard <xguimard@linagora.com>  Wed, 16 Apr 2026 20:00:00 +0200

open-bastion (0.1.2) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Mode E: Maximum Security (SSO certs only + sudo PAM-access + KRL)
  * --max-security option in ob-backend-setup and ob-bastion-setup
  * docker-demo-maxsec: Docker demo for Mode E architecture
  * CI integration tests for Mode E
  * EBIOS security study refactored for maximum security target
  * Fix OB_BASTION_JWT → LLNG_BASTION_JWT everywhere
  * Fix AllowAgentForwarding on bastion (no instead of yes)
  * Fix ProxyJump references: use ob-ssh-proxy for JWT injection
  * KRL format validation (SSHKRL magic bytes check)

 -- Xavier Guimard <xguimard@linagora.com>  Sun, 13 Apr 2026 12:00:00 +0200

open-bastion (0.1.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Supplementary groups synchronization via managed_groups configuration
  * Local whitelist for managed groups (allowed_managed_groups)
  * CrowdSec IP/CIDR whitelist to bypass checks for trusted IPs/networks
  * Fixed TOCTOU race condition in cache_key.c

